'''BMES''' (the '''Biomedical Engineering Society''') is the professional society for students, faculty, researcher and industry working in the broad area of [[biomedical engineering]]. BMES is the leading biomedical engineering society in the United States and was founded on February 1, 1968 "to promote the increase of [[biomedical engineering]] knowledge and its utilization." There are 7,000 members in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=Biomedical Engineering Society|url=http://bmes.org/about}}</ref>
