'''Komelon Co. Ltd.''' ([[hangul]]:코멜론주식회사, {{kosdaq|049430}}) is a [[South Korea|Korean]] [[chemical]], [[machinery]], [[tool]] and [[engineering]] company, headquartered in [[Busan]], [[Korea]]. Established in 1963, it manufactures [[plastic]] and [[steel]] [[tape measures]], [[level gauges]] and other [[tool]] products. The "Komelon" CEO is D.K. Kong and Bak Gi Seok (박기석). The company is commonly referred to as "Komelon" (Spelling '''Korea Motorized Electron''').
Komelon manufactures the Kobalt brand of tape measures for US-based home improvement chain [[Lowe's]].
